ES5

  • ” ECMAScript 3.1 became ECMA-262, fifth edition ” Page 51
  • ” a native JSON object for parsing and serializing JSON data, methods for inheritance and advanced property definition, and the inclusion of a new strict mode ” Page 51
  • JSON
  • Methods for inheritance - Inheritance Types
  • Strict Mode - Syntax-语法

ES6

  • ” The sixth edition of ECMA-262—colloquially referred to as ES6, ES2015, or ES Harmony ” Page 51
  • ” contains arguably the most important collection of enhancements ” Page 51
  • ” classes, modules, iterators, generators, arrow functions, promises, reflection, proxies, and a host of new data types. ” Page 51
  • Class (ES6 类)
  • C26-Modules
  • C-C07-Iterators and Generators
  • Function-函数 - Arrow Function
  • Promise
  • C09-Proxies and Reflect-代理与反射

ES7

  • ” The seventh edition of ECMA-262, dubbed ES7 or ES2016 ” Page 52
  • ” a handful of syntactical additions such as Array. prototype. includes and the exponentiation operator. ” Page 52

ES8

  • ” The eighth edition of ECMA-262, called ES8 or ES2017 ” Page 52
  • ” asynchronous iteration, rest and spread properties, a collection of new regular expression features, a Promise finally () catchall handler, and template literal revisions. ” Page 52
